"We will take the necessary steps to be ready for the law to be implemented as soon as it is signed", he added.
On the other hand, bad bank managers waiting for state aid can expect their start-up allowances, simply called the golden parachute across the Atlantic, to be capped by the government.
The limitation of wages is only mentioned in very specific cases, and the limitations depend on how the Treasury Secretariat offers its assistance to the enterprise.
The cap principle means that if the Treasury secretariat buys in an auction, they will take a surplus tax on the golden parachute, unless the discredited bank president retires.
Immediately after the redemption of the dubious debts, the government will intervene aggressively to ensure that the amount paid to the executives is not overstated.
To make the picture complete, it must be added that the existing gold parachutes are not modified, and the ceiling is only applied to new contracts, thus motivating participation in the plan.
